  "body": "- [ ] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nThe web3 instance provided in tests with truffle is still version 0.20.5. \r\nSome functions that are useful to make assertions do not work properly in this version:\r\neg. web3.toAscii still adds padding. \r\nThis is supposedly fixed in web1.0.0 with web3.utils.hexToAscii() or web3.utils.hexToUtf8()\r\n\r\nplease see https://github.com/ethereum/web3.js/issues/337\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n`AssertionError: Not the same name: expected 'John Doe' to equal 'John Doe\\u0000\\u0000\\u0000\\u0000\\u0000\\u0000\\u0000\\u0000\\u0000\\u0000\\u0000\\u0000\\u0000\\u0000\\u0000\\u0000\\u0000\\u0000\\u0000\\u0000\\u0000\\u0000\\u0000\\u0000'`\r\n\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Ubuntu 16.04\r\n* Ethereum client: Ganache \r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`):4.1.3\r\n\r\n",
